## üéØ Typical Workflow

### Water Damage Project

1. **Emergency Call** ‚Üí Create Work Order
2. **On-site Assessment** ‚Üí Create Dryout Project
3. **Document Loss** ‚Üí Photos, initial readings
4. **Equipment Deployment** ‚Üí Log all equipment
5. **Daily Monitoring** ‚Üí Moisture readings + photos
6. **Demolition** ‚Üí Document all demo work
7. **Drying Complete** ‚Üí Final readings, certificate
8. **Create Reconstruction Project** ‚Üí Link to dryout
9. **Build Estimate** ‚Üí Xactimate format
10. **Track Progress** ‚Üí Daily logs, photos
11. **Final Walkthrough** ‚Üí Completion certificate
12. **Invoice** ‚Üí Export to PDF, email

---

## üí° Pro Tips

### For Insurance Adjusters
- Always use Xactimate-compatible line codes
- Document EVERYTHING with photos
- Daily logs are your protection
- Keep moisture readings organized by date
- Track equipment rental days precisely

### For Estimates
- Include O&P (Overhead & Profit) - typically 20%
- Show line-item breakdown
- Reference Xactimate codes where possible
- Include all permits and inspections
- Document warranties

### For Documentation
- Take MORE photos than you think you need
- Date/time stamp everything
- Get client signatures on scope changes
- Keep daily logs even if "nothing happens"
- Document conversations with adjusters

